name: Divine
bio: Vivian Fernandes, known by his stage name Divine, is an Indian rapper from Mumbai. He gained popularity with the release of his song 'Meri Gully Mein' and is considered a pioneer of the Mumbai hip-hop scene.

name: Sidhu Moose Wala
bio: Shubhdeep Singh Sidhu, known as Sidhu Moose Wala, was a Punjabi singer, rapper, and songwriter associated with Punjabi music and cinema. He was renowned for his energetic performances and impactful lyrics.

name: Raftaar
bio: Dilin Nair, professionally known as Raftaar, is an Indian rapper, lyricist, dancer, and music composer. He began his career as a dancer before turning to music, where he gained fame for his rapid-fire rap style.

name: Yo Yo Honey Singh
bio: Hirdesh Singh, known by his professional name Yo Yo Honey Singh, is an Indian music producer, Indi-pop singer, and film actor. He started as a session and recording artist and became one of the highest-paid music producers in Bollywood.

name: Badshah
bio: Aditya Prateek Singh Sisodia, known by his stage name Badshah, is an Indian rapper and singer known for his Hindi, Haryanvi, and Punjabi songs. He started his career in 2006 alongside Yo Yo Honey Singh in his group Mafia Mundeer.

name: Emiway Bantai
bio: Bilal Shaikh, known professionally as Emiway Bantai, is an independent Indian rapper and hip-hop artist. He gained popularity with his song 'Machayenge' and is known for his independent approach to music.

name: MC Stan
bio: Altaf Shaikh, known professionally as MC Stan, is an Indian rapper, lyricist, and music producer. He is known for his unique style and has been a significant figure in the Indian hip-hop scene.

name: Brodha V
bio: Vighnesh Shivanand, known by his stage name Brodha V, is an Indian rapper, lyricist, and music producer. He is known for blending Indian classical music with hip-hop and has been a part of the Indian rap scene since the early 2000s.

name: Neha Kakkar
bio: Neha Kakkar is an Indian playback singer who began performing at religious events at the age of four. She participated in the second season of Indian Idol and has since become one of the most successful and popular playback singers in India.

name: Arijit Singh
bio: Arijit Singh is an Indian playback singer and music composer. He is known for his soulful voice and has been featured in numerous Bollywood films, making him one of the most successful and versatile singers in India.

name: Diljit Dosanjh
bio: Diljit Dosanjh is an Indian singer, actor, and television presenter who works in Punjabi and Hindi cinema. He is recognized as one of the leading artists in the Indian music industry and has also made a mark in acting.

name: King
bio: Arpan Kumar Chandel, known by his stage name King, is an Indian singer, rapper, and songwriter. He gained fame through his participation in the MTV reality show 'MTV Hustle' and is known for his versatile music style.

name: KRSNA
bio: Krishna Kaul, known by his stage name KRSNA, is an Indian rapper and songwriter. He is known for his lyrical prowess and has been a significant figure in the Indian hip-hop scene.

name: Jubin Nautiyal
bio: Jubin Nautiyal is an Indian playback singer and performer. He has recorded songs for various Bollywood films and has also released numerous independent singles.

name: Shreya Ghoshal
bio: Shreya Ghoshal is an Indian playback singer. She has received numerous awards and accolades and is one of the most established playback singers in India.

name: Guru Randhawa
bio: Guru Randhawa is an Indian singer, songwriter, and music composer known for his Punjabi, Bhangra, Indi-pop, and Bollywood music.

name: Drake
bio: Aubrey Drake Graham is a Canadian rapper, singer, and actor. Known for blending hip-hop with R&B, he gained fame with albums like 'Take Care' and 'Views,' dominating global charts.

name: Taylor Swift
bio: Taylor Swift is an American singer-songwriter known for her narrative-driven music across genres like pop, country, and indie. She’s one of the best-selling artists globally.

name: Beyoncé
bio: Beyoncé Knowles-Carter is an American singer, songwriter, and performer. A global icon, she’s celebrated for albums like 'Lemonade' and her dynamic live performances.

name: The Weeknd
bio: Abel Tesfaye, known as The Weeknd, is a Canadian singer and producer. His dark, cinematic style blends R&B and pop, with hits like 'Blinding Lights' dominating charts.

name: Billie Eilish
bio: Bill Iran Eilish is an American singer-songwriter known for her unique voice and genre-defying music. She rose to fame with 'Bad Guy' and won multiple Grammy Awards.

name: Ed Sheeran
bio: Ed Sheeran is a British singer-songwriter known for his soulful voice and acoustic-pop hits like 'Shape of You.' He’s a global chart-topper with a versatile style.

name: Adele
bio: Adele Laurie Blue Adkins is a British singer-songwriter renowned for her powerful vocals and emotional ballads like 'Hello.' She’s won numerous awards for her soulful music.

name: Kendrick Lamar
bio: Kendrick Lamar is an American rapper and songwriter known for his thought-provoking lyrics and albums like 'DAMN.' He’s a leading figure in modern hip-hop.

name: Rihanna
bio: Robyn Rihanna Fenty is a Barbadian singer, actress, and entrepreneur. Known for hits like 'Umbrella,' she’s a global pop icon with a versatile career.

name: Post Malone
bio: Austin Richard Post, known as Post Malone, is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter. His genre-blending style, seen in hits like 'Circles,' has made him a global star.
